[{"type":"message","text":"Hey there! I am doing a refresher of some algebra concepts while examining computational complexity. I went back through and re-derived an arithmetic sum but what confuses me from a textbook I am reading is the \"n\" in front of the quantity I circled. Where does this \"n\" come from? I cannot make it reappear through derivation so I am wondering if it is a degree of freedom or something simple I am missing. Any thoughts?","files":[{"id":"F01HSTFEXU6","created":1609811536,"timestamp":1609811536,"name":"image.png","title":"image.png","mimetype":"image/png","filetype":"png","pretty_type":"PNG","user":"US64J0NPQ","editable":false,"size":19088,"mode":"hosted","is_external":false,"external_type":"","is_public":true,"public_url_shared":false,"display_as_bot":false,"username":"","url_private":"https://files.slack.com/files-pri/T68168MUP-F01HSTFEXU6/image.png","url_private_download":"https://files.slack.com/files-pri/T68168MUP-F01HSTFEXU6/download/image.png","thumb_64":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01HSTFEXU6-a9a92b0feb/image_64.png","thumb_80":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01HSTFEXU6-a9a92b0feb/image_80.png","thumb_360":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01HSTFEXU6-a9a92b0feb/image_360.png","thumb_360_w":360,"thumb_360_h":245,"thumb_160":"https://files.slack.com/files-tmb/T68168MUP-F01HSTFEXU6-a9a92b0feb/image_160.png","original_w":465,"original_h":316,"thumb_tiny":"AwAgADCqvXpmjI/u/rQv0zS7XP8A+ugBDjsMUlO2v6Gja1ADaKXafSkII60AKozmgDrjk0lFADiefvGkboPWl3Gm0AFFFFAH/9k=","permalink":"https://julialang.slack.com/files/US64J0NPQ/F01HSTFEXU6/image.png","permalink_public":"https://slack-files.com/T68168MUP-F01HSTFEXU6-2384bb5ef3","is_starred":false,"has_rich_preview":false}],"upload":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"TjS","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Hey there! I am doing a refresher of some algebra concepts while examining computational complexity. I went back through and re-derived an arithmetic sum but what confuses me from a textbook I am reading is the \"n\" in front of the quantity I circled. Where does this \"n\" come from? I cannot make it reappear through derivation so I am wondering if it is a degree of freedom or something simple I am missing. Any thoughts?"}]}]}],"user":"US64J0NPQ","display_as_bot":false,"ts":"1609811555.114400","thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","reply_count":29,"reply_users_count":4,"latest_reply":"1609815543.121100","reply_users":["USU9FRPEU","U6788D83U","US64J0NPQ","UB197FRCL"],"subscribed":false},{"client_msg_id":"dbb21ee0-a04b-4106-bc07-162d388311dc","type":"message","text":"Well let's play with `n = 4` .","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811629.114700","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"1BBwz","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Well let's play with "},{"type":"text","text":"n = 4","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" ."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"5492cf6e-5c12-4124-982b-422d89f2a9bb","type":"message","text":"```julia&gt; a = 1:4\n1:4\n\njulia&gt; sum(a)\n10```","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811662.114900","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"0c2ja","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> a = 1:4\n1:4\n\njulia> sum(a)\n10"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"b292a47a-1a92-4a11-8828-47672e52a02f","type":"message","text":"right? so how we could get them from just looking at 1 and 4?","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811681.115200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"WbK","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"right? so how we could get them from just looking at 1 and 4?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"d03ff67f-f56a-4279-be01-3edb1c77e1b6","type":"message","text":"We could do:\n```julia&gt; a[1] + a[end]\n5\n\njulia&gt; a[2] + a[end-1]\n5```","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811713.115400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"iP4uG","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We could do:\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> a[1] + a[end]\n5\n\njulia> a[2] + a[end-1]\n5"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"9df65d67-443e-4516-9c69-0443ba9a7e20","type":"message","text":"and then obviously\n```julia&gt; 5+5\n10\n\njulia&gt; 2*5\n10```","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811752.115600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"WGo","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"and then obviously\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> 5+5\n10\n\njulia> 2*5\n10"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"52485007-40d0-4699-846b-612523d3e863","type":"message","text":"```julia&gt; 4/2 * (4 + 1)\n10.0```","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811791.115800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"yNh","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> 4/2 * (4 + 1)\n10.0"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"9ca64886-6211-40d3-a0d8-e37f4787a401","type":"message","text":"So what did we do... we grouped the first and last ... added that up. That equals `n+1`","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811817.116000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"l4D6","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"So what did we do... we grouped the first and last ... added that up. That equals "},{"type":"text","text":"n+1","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"9439232d-b25f-4d8a-87e7-243fb3b36ce5","type":"message","text":"then we took the second and the second to last, added that up, that also equals `n+1`","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811833.116200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"4JVL","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"then we took the second and the second to last, added that up, that also equals "},{"type":"text","text":"n+1","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"50b33ef8-b594-487c-b540-c87367fd9517","type":"message","text":"We ended up two groups of `n+1` when `n=4`","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811849.116400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"wAA","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We ended up two groups of "},{"type":"text","text":"n+1","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" when "},{"type":"text","text":"n=4","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"9e5b251c-57cd-46e1-84f9-489bb97466ef","type":"message","text":"Let's try `n=6` now.","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811867.116600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"85b","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let's try "},{"type":"text","text":"n=6","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" now."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"dbf684c1-1f0e-4fc1-b816-a9b0dd0a847d","type":"message","text":"Basically, let `s = sum(1:n)`. We have\n```2s = 1+2+3+...+n\n    +n+...+3+2+1\n   = n*(n+1)```\nso\n```s = n*(n+1)/2```","user":"U6788D83U","ts":"1609811883.116800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"W1V=L","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Basically, let "},{"type":"text","text":"s = sum(1:n)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":". We have\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"2s = 1+2+3+...+n\n    +n+...+3+2+1\n   = n*(n+1)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"so\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"s = n*(n+1)/2"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"3be06b3c-46cf-49fe-a8ec-673b6c1fea5e","type":"message","text":"```julia&gt; a[1] + a[end], a[2] + a[end-1], a[3] + a[end-2]\n(7, 7, 7)```\n","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811906.117000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"hn6Fl","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> a[1] + a[end], a[2] + a[end-1], a[3] + a[end-2]\n(7, 7, 7)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"36d52a2e-7220-4f53-aa00-244c4d2e7700","type":"message","text":"So we know that when `iseven(n)` we will have `n/2` groups that add up to `n+1`","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609811935.117200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"viRn/","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"So we know that when "},{"type":"text","text":"iseven(n)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" we will have "},{"type":"text","text":"n/2","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" groups that add up to "},{"type":"text","text":"n+1","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"896344b5-8a64-4933-9e6d-01ec7840acaa","type":"message","text":"When is `n` is odd, you end up with `(n-1)/2` groups  that add up to `n+1` and a single number that is `(n+1)/2` .\n```julia&gt; a = 1:5\n1:5\n\njulia&gt; a[1] + a[end], a[2] + a[end-1], a[3]\n(6, 6, 3)```\nSo that's `(n+1)(n-1)/2 + (n+1)/2 = n(n+1)/2`","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609812383.117400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"VJy","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"When is "},{"type":"text","text":"n","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is odd, you end up with "},{"type":"text","text":"(n-1)/2","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" groups  that add up to "},{"type":"text","text":"n+1","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and a single number that is "},{"type":"text","text":"(n+1)/2","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" .\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> a = 1:5\n1:5\n\njulia> a[1] + a[end], a[2] + a[end-1], a[3]\n(6, 6, 3)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"\nSo that's "},{"type":"text","text":"(n+1)(n-1)/2 + (n+1)/2 = n(n+1)/2","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"c6a197fa-26ec-444e-85b0-68e96dfb01e5","type":"message","text":"Do either of those answers help?","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609812422.117600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"xLYN","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Do either of those answers help?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609811555.114400","parent_user_id":"US64J0NPQ"},{"client_msg_id":"0cb1535d-9c28-47e5-914d-c64f2a00e07a","type":"message","text":"Oh absolutely <@USU9FRPEU> and <@U6788D83U> ! Just convincing myself of the steps you took. Give me just a few more minutes. :slightly_smiling_face:","user":"US64J0NPQ","ts":"1609812475.117800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"4mGL","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Oh absolutely "},{"type":"user","user_id":"USU9FRPEU"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"user","user_id":"U6788D83U"},{"type":"text","text":" ! Just convincing myself of the steps you took. Give me just a few more minutes. "},{"type":"emoji","name":"slight